Need to steal a few fucking supplies.

26:51.234 --> 26:54.529
-That's not a bad day's work.
-Ricky! Listen to yourself though.

26:54.612 --> 26:56.573
The whole point of you getting
into business for yourself

26:56.656 --> 26:58.908
is so that you don't have
to break the law anymore.

26:58.992 --> 27:00.076
I'm not.

27:00.160 --> 27:03.038
You just said you're
gonna steal supplies.

27:03.121 --> 27:06.875
Like, stealing is not allowed anymore,
Ricky, that's what I'm saying.

27:07.167 --> 27:08.501
If you wanna turn
your life around,

27:08.585 --> 27:11.338
you make an honest living
being your own boss.

27:11.421 --> 27:13.923
-That's how you do it.
-Boys, check it out!

27:14.007 --> 27:15.717
I got a job at the mall.

27:15.800 --> 27:19.387
I just put in a four-hour shift.
I fucking loved it, man. It was awesome!

27:19.471 --> 27:21.639
A job at the mall?
Doing what?

27:22.182 --> 27:24.392
Oh, Ricky, come on. It's... Look.

27:25.060 --> 27:27.187
He's a cashier, Ricky.

27:27.270 --> 27:29.022
-[giggling]
-I'm a security man.

27:29.105 --> 27:30.482
-That's amazing!
-Yeah, man.

27:30.565 --> 27:33.026
You've got a real job.
You're a working man!

27:33.109 --> 27:36.404
-[Julian] Damn rights, buddy.
-Unbelievable. I'm proud of you, Julian.

27:36.488 --> 27:38.073
I'm very proud of you.

27:38.615 --> 27:39.991
Very proud. Ricky...

27:40.075 --> 27:41.993
Ricky got a legit job today too.

27:42.077 --> 27:44.662
No way. Doing what, carpentry?

27:45.038 --> 27:46.664
How the fuck did you know that?

27:46.998 --> 27:48.333
Ricky, I'm proud of you too.

27:48.416 --> 27:50.001
-Get in here.
-Get over here, man.

27:50.085 --> 27:51.669
-Get in here!
-Are you kidding me?

27:51.753 --> 27:53.671
-Huggie wuggies time.
-All right, buddy!

27:53.755 --> 27:55.507
[Cory] Aw, dudes,
I love hugs!

27:55.965 --> 27:57.217
Look, man.

27:57.300 --> 27:58.968
Fucking hero, dude,
I found one.

27:59.052 --> 28:01.137
But the rest are all broken.
What should I do?

28:01.221 --> 28:02.972
Maybe, Cory, maybe
you should go down

28:03.056 --> 28:05.433
and fucking ram them
in your stupid piss-hole.

28:05.517 --> 28:07.310
-[Ricky laughing]
-Why don't you do that?

28:07.977 --> 28:10.855
Cory, go clean up
the fucking bottles! Go!

28:10.939 --> 28:13.358
Don't ruin beautiful moments, Cory!

28:13.733 --> 28:15.318
Fuck's sakes!

28:16.194 --> 28:17.862
[sighing] Get back in here!

28:17.946 --> 28:19.739
I'm not giving up on my hugs.

28:19.823 --> 28:21.282
-[giggling]
-Right on, boys.

28:21.366 --> 28:23.993
My two best friends
making an honest living.

28:24.369 --> 28:25.620
Right, Ricky?

28:25.703 --> 28:27.539
-Right, Bubs.
-Honest.

28:27.622 --> 28:30.250
-Right on, man.
-Boys... if I was a kitty,

28:30.333 --> 28:33.711
you guys'd both need earplugs right now,
I'd be purring so loud!

28:34.003 --> 28:35.255
[giggling]

28:35.338 --> 28:37.173
[purring]

